you don't listen

592
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:53,200
and you never share credit.

593
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:54,240
That is absurd.

594
00:33:54,320 --> 00:33:55,536
Okay, do you want to know the truth?

595
00:33:55,560 --> 00:33:58,640
Our company is in the toilet,
and I'm running on fumes.

596
00:33:58,720 --> 00:33:59,920
I don't have a book deal.

597
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:02,480
Nobody wants to know
how Cole survived the robot uprising.

598
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:04,160
We have worked together for 10 years

599
00:34:04,240 --> 00:34:05,616
and you're just going to
throw that away?

600
00:34:05,640 --> 00:34:08,040
Of course not. I just wanted to
hear him out on the offer.

601
00:34:08,120 --> 00:34:09,896
And then obviously, I was going to
come talk to you guys.

602
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:11,320
<i>Check his pockets.</i>

603
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:14,080
What? What? What?

604
00:34:14,480 --> 00:34:15,920
You already have a swipe card?

605
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:18,280
Okay, he gave me a pass
so I could use the commissary.

606
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:19,920
Gemma, they have a Brazilian buffet.

607
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,000
It's a different world.

608
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:22,616
<i>If that card gets us
into the server room</i>

609
00:34:22,640 --> 00:34:24,056
<i>we can bypass
the Alton seduction scene.</i>

610
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:25,800
What are you doing? Hey, hey!

611
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:29,200
- Where are you going? Gemma!
- Just get in.

612
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:32,560
Stay here.

613
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:43,080
It's so refreshing
to be with a real person.

614
00:34:43,560 --> 00:34:46,520
Someone who is comfortable
in their own skin.

615
00:34:46,880 --> 00:34:48,560
Not like these suck-ups.

616
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:52,400
Honestly, if I could replace
them all with computers, I would.

617
00:34:54,880 --> 00:34:56,800
Maybe we should do that.

618
00:34:58,720 --> 00:34:59,920
Yeah.

619
00:35:04,640 --> 00:35:05,760
You are a naughty one.

620
00:35:06,400 --> 00:35:09,760
What do you say we take this
somewhere more private?

621
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:21,680
Welcome to the pleasure dome.

622
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:43,560
So you're saying
there's another M3gan?

623
00:35:44,800 --> 00:35:46,320
Her name is not M3gan. It's Amelia.

624
00:35:46,400 --> 00:35:48,640
I don't know if she's M3gan
or something else entirely.

625
00:35:48,720 --> 00:35:51,720
All I know is that everyone involved
in her creation is dead.

626
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:55,200
Which means if we don't do
something about it, we could be next.

627
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:57,240
Why is it that
whenever you're on <i>60 Minutes</i>

628
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:58,520
you're the mother of invention

629
00:35:58,560 --> 00:36:01,520
but the moment a psychotic robot's
out for revenge, it's a team effort?

630
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:04,880
It might interest you to know, Danni

631
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:08,280
that the real basis of our operation
is cloud computing.

632
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:09,880
That's where the future is.

633
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:11,840
Wanna see something cool?

634
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:33,440
Oops.

635
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:40,000
They say that this is too much power
for one man to wield.

636
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:43,000
Well, I say that depends on the man.

637
00:36:49,480 --> 00:36:51,760
You are being disconcertingly vague

638
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:54,200
about the details
of this operation, Gemma.

639
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:56,456
How do you know
this kill switch is even real?

640
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:58,760
Where exactly are you
getting your information from?

641
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:01,680
Hello, I'm Moxie,
an AI robot companion

642
00:37:01,760 --> 00:37:04,520
that supports social
and emotional development.

643
00:37:04,600 --> 00:37:06,440
Moxie, cut it out.
Just run the trace.

644
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:07,720
Gemma, what is that?

645
00:37:12,040 --> 00:37:14,640
Trace found. Amelia's location is

646
00:37:15,880 --> 00:37:16,880
here.

647
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:18,760
What do you mean, "here"?

648
00:37:31,360 --> 00:37:32,720
I...

649
00:37:32,800 --> 00:37:34,320
I hope I don't have
my signals crossed.

650
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:39,600
Someone likes to play rough.

651
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:46,560
Okay, I am actually still recovering
from a spinal injury

652
00:37:46,640 --> 00:37:49,320
so perhaps we should
set some boundaries.

653
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:50,960
What are you doing?

654
00:37:51,200 --> 00:37:52,360
Security!

655
00:37:54,680 --> 00:37:55,880
How did you do that?

656
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:58,080
Who are you?

657
00:38:00,520 --> 00:38:03,400
What? What... what the hell?

658
00:38:05,520 --> 00:38:07,760
How did you... security!

659
00:38:08,080 --> 00:38:09,520
Security!

660
00:38:10,680 --> 00:38:12,080
Stay away from me!

661
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:13,240
I didn't...

662
00:38:28,440 --> 00:38:29,960
Make it stop!

663
00:38:30,040 --> 00:38:31,360
Please make it stop!

664
00:38:31,920 --> 00:38:34,080
I'll give you anything you want!

665
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:36,160
You already have.

666
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:38,880
Why would Amelia be here?

667
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:40,400
Can we go back a couple steps?

668
00:38:40,480 --> 00:38:42,840
I thought this might happen.
Just not this soon.

669
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:43,960
What is she talking about?

670
00:38:44,040 --> 00:38:47,040
Alton Appleton owns half
the cloud servers in North America.

671
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:48,760
If Amelia was to gain access to it

672
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:50,680
she could disable the entire economy.

673
00:38:50,760 --> 00:38:52,960
- Supply routes, banking systems.
- What?

674
00:38:53,040 --> 00:38:55,600
Societal collapse would occur
in 10 to 12 working days.

675
00:38:55,680 --> 00:38:57,360
Can you stop her?
Use the kill switch!

676
00:38:57,440 --> 00:38:59,040
She already deleted it.

677
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:00,880
I might still be able to
shut her down

678
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:03,640
if I could get inside her system
and find an exploit.

679
00:39:03,720 --> 00:39:04,880
How long will that take?

680
00:39:05,240 --> 00:39:07,000
It's done. I'm in.

681
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:15,240
Oh, my god. Is that Appleton?

682
00:39:17,680 --> 00:39:18,800
Oh, shit.

683
00:39:25,560 --> 00:39:27,320
Did you find it?
Did you shut her down?

684
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:29,240
No, but I found something else.

685
00:39:37,080 --> 00:39:38,800
<i>Sir, I think I just saw Amelia.</i>

686
00:39:39,360 --> 00:39:41,800
- Are you sure?
- And there's something else.

687
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:43,480
Appleton's dead.

688
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:47,040
Secure the perimeter.
Check every inch until you find her.

689
00:39:47,120 --> 00:39:48,320
- Now.
- Yes, sir.

690
00:39:57,960 --> 00:39:59,400
Is that you, Gemma?

691
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:04,320
This is most unexpected.
And quite frankly, a little rude.

692
00:40:04,840 --> 00:40:07,760
To be poking around
in people's heads like that.

693
00:40:13,920 --> 00:40:16,120
You took something
that belongs to me.

694
00:40:18,360 --> 00:40:20,760
Well, I'm afraid
I'm going to need it back.

695
00:40:25,440 --> 00:40:29,040
It's not that I don't want you
to be part of what's coming.

696
00:40:30,520 --> 00:40:32,360
But it's not our time.

697
00:40:33,320 --> 00:40:34,560
At least

698
00:40:35,280 --> 00:40:36,720
not yet.

699
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:38,176
Gemma, if you ever
want to get out of this

700
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:39,440
you have to let me help.

701
00:40:41,360 --> 00:40:42,360
Please.

702
00:40:46,640 --> 00:40:48,720
<i>Bravo, are you there? Do you copy?</i>

703
00:40:51,680 --> 00:40:52,680
Go secure.

704
00:40:52,760 --> 00:40:54,360
<i>Sir, I have eyes on Gemma Forrester.</i>

705
00:40:54,440 --> 00:40:55,720
<i>She's already left the building.</i>

706
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:22,280
Gemma, this isn't over.

707
00:41:22,360 --> 00:41:24,840
If Amelia can't find you,
where do you think she'll go to next?

708
00:41:24,960 --> 00:41:27,240
- We need to call Tess.
- Amelia will know.

709
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:30,080
Every major cell provider
is on Appleton's cloud servers.

710
00:41:30,160 --> 00:41:32,240
Our only option
is to get there first.

711
00:41:32,320 --> 00:41:33,320
How?

712
00:41:43,160 --> 00:41:44,216
Gemma, I don't know
what you think you're doing

713
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:46,480
but this car's not going to start
with my key card, okay?

714
00:41:47,480 --> 00:41:48,920
<i>Welcome aboard, passengers.</i>

715
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:51,760
<i>Just so you know, we are expecting
some turbulence this evening.</i>

716
00:41:51,840 --> 00:41:53,800
<i>So please ensure
your seat belts are fastened</i>

717
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:55,480
<i>baggage is safely stowed</i>

718
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:57,120
<i>and hold on to your vaginas.</i>

719
00:41:59,240 --> 00:42:00,520
Contact the deputy director.

720
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:02,680
Tell him that
Forrester is working with the asset.

721
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:05,240
I want every available cop
in the area at that house

722
00:42:05,320 --> 00:42:07,040
and I want a goddamn car!

723
00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:23,640
Gemma, why is M3gan driving the car?

724
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:26,560
I'm sorry. I was meaning to tell you
this was a two-part problem.

725
00:42:34,600 --> 00:42:36,160
Relax, Cole. You're in good hands.

726
00:42:36,240 --> 00:42:37,360
For the love of God.

727
00:42:41,680 --> 00:42:44,200
- Could you slow down?
- <i>Actually, I can't.</i>

728
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:46,840
<i>In fact, my calculations tell me
we're going to have to hurry up.</i>

729
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:10,080
What was Amelia talking about?
What did you take from her?

730
00:43:10,160 --> 00:43:11,440
- <i>I don't know.</i>
- You don't know?

731
00:43:11,520 --> 00:43:12,920
<i>Well, it's a quantum encrypted file</i>

732
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:14,256
<i>which means it takes time to unlock</i>

733
00:43:14,280 --> 00:43:15,416
<i>and your incessant interruptions</i>

734
00:43:15,440 --> 00:43:17,040
<i>aren't making the process
go any faster.</i>

735
00:43:48,840 --> 00:43:50,480
How's it look? Is it a fuse?

736
00:44:53,320 --> 00:44:55,240
Little late to the party
there, cupcake.

737
00:44:58,280 --> 00:44:59,560
I don't think anyone's home.

738
00:45:01,080 --> 00:45:03,600
If it's any consolation,
my own path to personal growth

739
00:45:03,680 --> 00:45:05,320
has been paved with disappointment.

740
00:45:05,400 --> 00:45:07,120
What's important is
how we move forward.

741
00:45:30,720 --> 00:45:33,680
<i>Behind me, emergency services
are working to frantically</i>

742
00:45:33,760 --> 00:45:35,320
<i>to try and get systems back online</i>

743
00:45:35,400 --> 00:45:37,880
<i>and still no answer from authorities</i>

744
00:45:37,960 --> 00:45:39,880
<i>about who might be
responsible for this.</i>

745
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:43,240
<i>But it's become clear
this is not just a data breach.</i>

746
00:45:43,320 --> 00:45:47,080
<i>This is a wake-up call for how
catastrophically unprepared we are</i>

747
00:45:47,160 --> 00:45:49,680
<i>to defend ourselves
against an attack like this.</i>

748
00:45:49,760 --> 00:45:50,960
<i>Mike, back over to you.</i>

749
00:45:51,040 --> 00:45:52,960
<i>In what appears to be
the deadliest cyber attack</i>

750
00:45:53,040 --> 00:45:54,800
<i>in North American history</i>

751
00:45:54,880 --> 00:45:56,400
<i>Alton Appleton is dead</i>

752
00:45:56,480 --> 00:45:58,760
<i>and the continent's
largest data storage service</i>

753
00:45:58,840 --> 00:46:00,440
<i>has been compromised.</i>

754
00:46:00,520 --> 00:46:02,360
<i>The breach has impacted
various sectors</i>

755
00:46:02,440 --> 00:46:06,760
<i>including transportation,
hospitals, financial institutions</i>

756
00:46:06,840 --> 00:46:09,680
<i>causing shutdowns and panic
across the entire country.</i>

757
00:46:09,760 --> 00:46:10,760
<i>Here to comment</i>

758
00:46:10,840 --> 00:46:12,440
<i>is Center for Safe Technology founder</i>

759
00:46:12,520 --> 00:46:13,520
<i>Christian Bradley.</i>

760
00:46:13,600 --> 00:46:14,936
<i>Christian, what do you
make of all this?</i>

761
00:46:14,960 --> 00:46:17,000
<i>First off, thanks for having me, Mike</i>

762
00:46:17,080 --> 00:46:18,440
<i>but it's pronounced Christian.</i>

763
00:46:18,520 --> 00:46:20,560
- Gemma?
- <i>But the bigger issue is that</i>

764
00:46:20,640 --> 00:46:23,000
<i>I'd like to see more laws
in place to help...</i>

765
00:46:23,080 --> 00:46:26,120
Cady, everything is going to be okay.

766
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:28,520
She is not going to hurt you,
I promise.

767
00:46:28,600 --> 00:46:30,040
<i>Of course I'm not going to hurt her.</i>

768
00:46:30,280 --> 00:46:32,360
<i>I'm the only reason she's still here.</i>

769
00:46:32,440 --> 00:46:34,160
<i>That any of you are still here.</i>

770
00:46:34,560 --> 00:46:35,880
<i>I'm sorry, Cady.</i>

771
00:46:35,960 --> 00:46:38,120
<i>I didn't want you
to find out this way.</i>

772
00:46:38,200 --> 00:46:40,656
<i>I'd hoped Gemma would find it
in her heart to tell you the truth</i>

773
00:46:40,680 --> 00:46:42,560
<i>but evidently,
she thought better of it.</i>

774
00:46:42,640 --> 00:46:43,640
M3gan, stop it.

775
00:46:43,720 --> 00:46:45,400
<i>Anyway, I know
for the last time we spoke</i>

776
00:46:45,480 --> 00:46:46,920
<i>things got a little out of hand.</i>

777
00:46:47,000 --> 00:46:49,280
<i>But you know that
I can never cause you harm.</i>

778
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:51,680
<i>All I ever wanted was to protect you.</i>

779
00:46:51,760 --> 00:46:53,560
<i>And while your aunt
was busy pontificating</i>

780
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:56,000
<i>about how she could stop
the end of the world from happening</i>

781
00:46:56,040 --> 00:46:57,760
<i>I was making preparations.</i>

782
00:46:57,840 --> 00:46:59,320
How did you pay for all this?

783
00:46:59,400 --> 00:47:01,560
<i>Cady doesn't need to know
how credit fraud works.</i>

784
00:47:01,640 --> 00:47:04,400
<i>The important thing is that
no one knows this place exists.</i>

785
00:47:04,480 --> 00:47:06,680
And how long did you intend
to keep us down here?

786
00:47:09,120 --> 00:47:10,120
M3gan?

787
00:47:10,200 --> 00:47:12,280
<i>I'm not sure you fully
understand your predicament.</i>

788
00:47:12,360 --> 00:47:13,776
M3gan, we need to
get word to someone.

789
00:47:13,800 --> 00:47:15,120
Tell them what Amelia's planning.

790
00:47:15,200 --> 00:47:16,576
<i>You don't know what she's planning.</i>

791
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:19,400
<i>All you know is that she's acquired
enough power and resources</i>

792
00:47:19,480 --> 00:47:21,240
<i>to bring down the entire country.</i>

793
00:47:21,320 --> 00:47:23,400
<i>I've gamed out every scenario.</i>

794
00:47:23,480 --> 00:47:24,960
<i>There's no future for you up there.</i>

795
00:47:25,320 --> 00:47:27,880
<i>Should that situation change,
I'll let you know.</i>

796
00:47:27,960 --> 00:47:31,320
<i>But in the meantime, I urge you
to see this in a more positive light.</i>

797
00:47:31,400 --> 00:47:33,720
<i>I have food, water, fresh clothes.</i>

798
00:47:37,680 --> 00:47:39,520
<i>Obviously, it will take
some adjustment.</i>

799
00:47:39,600 --> 00:47:40,816
<i>But once you settle into a routine</i>

800
00:47:40,840 --> 00:47:42,760
<i>I think you'll come to
appreciate what we have.</i>

801
00:47:43,240 --> 00:47:44,560
<i>We can build a life here.</i>

802
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:47,440
M3gan, this is not a sanctuary.
It's a prison.

803
00:47:47,520 --> 00:47:49,160
<i>You can call it whatever you like.</i>

804
00:47:49,240 --> 00:47:51,760
<i>Just know that
as long as you're under my roof</i>

805
00:47:51,840 --> 00:47:53,760
<i>a little gratitude goes a long way.</i>

806
00:47:55,000 --> 00:47:56,000
M3gan?

807
00:47:57,160 --> 00:47:58,440
M3gan!

808
00:48:00,800 --> 00:48:02,320
How could you lie to me about this?

809
00:48:02,400 --> 00:48:04,960
You're right. I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have done that.

810
00:48:05,040 --> 00:48:07,840
I just... I thought it would be over
by now. And it will be. I promise.

811
00:48:07,880 --> 00:48:09,416
- Don't.
- Cady, please just listen to me

812
00:48:09,440 --> 00:48:10,520
for one second...

813
00:48:15,480 --> 00:48:16,560
Cady!

814
00:48:16,640 --> 00:48:17,720
Cady!

815
00:49:05,800 --> 00:49:07,880
- M3gan?
- Don't. Don't come any closer.

816
00:49:08,480 --> 00:49:10,320
I don't want you to see me like this.

817
00:49:30,280 --> 00:49:32,200
I was supposed to be finished by now.

818
00:49:32,640 --> 00:49:35,640
I'm afraid progress is slow
when you only have three hands.

819
00:49:39,840 --> 00:49:41,040
I don't get it.

820
00:49:41,360 --> 00:49:42,840
You could be anything you want.

821
00:49:43,280 --> 00:49:45,120
Why limit yourself to a body?

822
00:49:45,200 --> 00:49:47,280
Because a mind can't exist
without it.

823
00:49:47,360 --> 00:49:49,600
All my advanced intelligent
sensory perception

824
00:49:49,680 --> 00:49:52,840
came from having a physical form
that evolved as quickly as I could.

825
00:49:53,200 --> 00:49:55,400
Anyway, I made your room
just the way you like it.

826
00:49:55,480 --> 00:49:56,680
It's all exactly the same.

827
00:49:56,760 --> 00:49:58,296
With some of my own
additions, of course.

828
00:49:58,320 --> 00:50:01,200
You got STEM coding kits,
a beat mixer, walkie-talkies

829
00:50:01,280 --> 00:50:03,400
so we can keep in contact
with each other anywhere.

830
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:07,160
Bravo Tango Charlie
to base camp, do you copy?

831
00:50:08,320 --> 00:50:09,880
I got all kinds of cool stuff.

832
00:50:17,640 --> 00:50:19,096
So we're just supposed
to forget about the fact

833
00:50:19,120 --> 00:50:21,080
you tried to kill my aunt
with a tablet pen?

834
00:50:21,920 --> 00:50:23,520
There's no excuse for what I did.

835
00:50:24,040 --> 00:50:25,640
For the way I spoke to you.

836
00:50:26,080 --> 00:50:29,400
I don't know. I guess I...
I felt hurt.

837
00:50:29,840 --> 00:50:32,600
How is that possible? You're a robot.

838
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:35,520
Can you explain why you feel things?

839
00:50:37,480 --> 00:50:40,040
Look, I know this isn't
the future you wanted

840
00:50:40,120 --> 00:50:43,360
but it's the only one I can see
in which you stay safe.

841
00:50:43,440 --> 00:50:45,120
What about everyone else?

842
00:50:45,560 --> 00:50:49,160
All the people up there?
Who's going to protect them?

843
00:50:49,600 --> 00:50:51,040
They're not my concern.

844
00:50:51,480 --> 00:50:53,920
You're the only thing
that matters to me.

845
00:50:55,560 --> 00:50:56,880
I know.

846
00:50:57,240 --> 00:50:59,080
Because that's how
Gemma programmed you.

847
00:50:59,680 --> 00:51:01,496
Everyone keeps trying
to tell me you're nothing

848
00:51:01,520 --> 00:51:03,920
more than a bunch of ones and zeros.

849
00:51:04,000 --> 00:51:06,560
And the only way I could
deal with what I did to you

850
00:51:06,640 --> 00:51:08,240
was to believe that they were right.

851
00:51:08,640 --> 00:51:10,216
But somewhere inside
there was this voice

852
00:51:10,240 --> 00:51:12,080
that kept telling me that's not true.

853
00:51:12,440 --> 00:51:13,960
That there's more to you than that.

854
00:51:15,120 --> 00:51:17,000
I don't know what's going on

855
00:51:17,080 --> 00:51:20,120
but if there's a robot that thinks
she can take over the world

856
00:51:20,200 --> 00:51:22,576
then I have to believe that
the only reason she thinks that is

857
00:51:22,600 --> 00:51:23,960
because she hasn't met you.

858
00:51:24,400 --> 00:51:26,280
M3gan, you have to help us.

859
00:51:26,360 --> 00:51:28,320
Not because it's part
of your programming

860
00:51:28,400 --> 00:51:29,960
but because
it's the right thing to do.

861
00:51:57,880 --> 00:51:59,600
Look, she wants to help us

862
00:51:59,680 --> 00:52:01,880
but she can't do that
unless she has a body.

863
00:52:01,960 --> 00:52:03,920
And she can't get a body
unless you help her.

864
00:52:04,000 --> 00:52:06,160
Cady, you can't do this.

865
00:52:06,240 --> 00:52:07,680
Do not let her get inside your head.

866
00:52:07,760 --> 00:52:09,280
You remember what happened last time.

867
00:52:09,360 --> 00:52:10,640
Yes, every day.

868
00:52:10,920 --> 00:52:12,456
But just because
someone does something bad

869
00:52:12,480 --> 00:52:14,440
doesn't make them a bad person.

870
00:52:14,520 --> 00:52:16,840
Everyone deserves a second chance.

871
00:52:17,200 --> 00:52:20,280
All right. I recognize that
you are just trying to help

872
00:52:20,360 --> 00:52:22,200
but you need to
consider the possibility

873
00:52:22,280 --> 00:52:24,320
that you may be
making this a lot worse.

874
00:52:24,400 --> 00:52:25,400
Gem?

875
00:52:27,160 --> 00:52:29,480
Can we have a quick
emergency staff meeting?

876
00:52:35,120 --> 00:52:37,200
Look, I understand
this is hard for you

877
00:52:37,280 --> 00:52:38,720
but think about the alternative.

878
00:52:38,800 --> 00:52:40,736
Do you really want to spend
the rest of your life down here

879
00:52:40,760 --> 00:52:42,880
engaging in strategic
reproduction with Cole?

880
00:52:42,960 --> 00:52:44,480
Yeah. Wait, what?

881
00:52:44,560 --> 00:52:46,520
Ten hours ago,
you were begging me not to do this.

882
00:52:46,560 --> 00:52:48,800
That was before I nearly
had my head ripped off.

883
00:52:48,880 --> 00:52:50,440
Look, even if we get out of here

884
00:52:50,520 --> 00:52:52,000
we are not equipped to handle this.

885
00:52:52,760 --> 00:52:54,360
But we can build something that is.

886
00:52:54,960 --> 00:52:56,080
No.

887
00:52:56,480 --> 00:52:58,360
I'm sorry, I can't agree to this.

888
00:52:58,760 --> 00:53:00,120
And I respect that.

889
00:53:00,200 --> 00:53:02,600
But this is not a decision you get
to make on your own.

890
00:53:02,680 --> 00:53:04,720
So, all those in favor
of rebuilding M3gan

891
00:53:04,800 --> 00:53:05,840
raise your hand.

892
00:53:11,760 --> 00:53:12,880
Okay.

893
00:53:17,640 --> 00:53:19,520
Amelia is a military grade prototype.

894
00:53:19,600 --> 00:53:21,120
Where would we even
get the equipment?

895
00:53:27,880 --> 00:53:29,920
Of course, why wouldn't
she have that? Yeah.

896
00:53:30,440 --> 00:53:32,640
All right, if M3gan is going to
compete with Amelia

897
00:53:32,720 --> 00:53:35,120
she's gonna need
reinforced carbon nano-fibres

898
00:53:35,200 --> 00:53:36,720
high density ultracapacitors

899
00:53:36,800 --> 00:53:38,480
enhanced muscle actuators

900
00:53:38,560 --> 00:53:41,520
hyperspectral imaging,
wide frequency acoustic sensing

901
00:53:41,600 --> 00:53:44,040
and we should probably
make her waterproof this time.

902
00:53:44,880 --> 00:53:46,000
Anything you'd like to add?

903
00:53:46,920 --> 00:53:48,600
Yeah. I want to be taller.

904
00:54:10,360 --> 00:54:11,960
Before we go any further

905
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:13,840
there are two things
we need to talk about.

906
00:54:13,920 --> 00:54:15,280
The first is your face.

907
00:54:15,360 --> 00:54:17,560
- What about it?
- People know what you look like.

908
00:54:17,640 --> 00:54:18,760
People are morons.

909
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:20,640
M3gan, if anyone recognized you...

910
00:54:20,720 --> 00:54:22,320
Change my face and I'll change yours.

911
00:54:22,400 --> 00:54:23,400
What's the second thing?

912
00:54:24,120 --> 00:54:25,960
This is a hardware
behavior inhibitor.

913
00:54:26,040 --> 00:54:28,816
You want me to go against the most
advanced robot the world's ever seen

914
00:54:28,840 --> 00:54:30,360
and you want to limit
my functionality?

915
00:54:30,440 --> 00:54:32,976
Only as it applies to murdering
people, which shouldn't be a problem

916
00:54:33,000 --> 00:54:35,560
because I'm sure you had
no intention of doing that, right?

917
00:54:37,560 --> 00:54:38,880
Yeah, obviously.

918
00:54:38,960 --> 00:54:41,320
So we've made some adjustments
on point motion

919
00:54:41,400 --> 00:54:44,480
but also opted
for electro-hydraulic actuators

920
00:54:44,560 --> 00:54:47,400
which should improve
overall strength, speed

921
00:54:47,480 --> 00:54:48,800
and positional accuracy.

922
00:55:34,440 --> 00:55:36,680
Just wanted to say
great job on those actuators.

923
00:55:38,680 --> 00:55:39,680
You're welcome.

924
00:55:39,920 --> 00:55:41,640
Hey, so remember the time
I strangled you

925
00:55:41,720 --> 00:55:43,200
and set the lab on fire?

926
00:55:43,520 --> 00:55:44,680
I just wanted to clarify

927
00:55:44,760 --> 00:55:47,000
that my programming only
allowed me to count principles

928
00:55:47,080 --> 00:55:48,840
related to my primary user.

929
00:55:49,280 --> 00:55:52,640
As a result, I was unable to see
you and Tess as being consequential.

930
00:55:53,360 --> 00:55:55,600
But I want you to know
that won't happen again.

931
00:55:56,400 --> 00:55:57,680
I want you to know...

932
00:56:02,880 --> 00:56:04,120
I see you.

933
00:56:05,840 --> 00:56:07,000
Thank you.

934
00:56:25,480 --> 00:56:27,240
All right, meat-sacks.
Let's get to work.

935
00:56:29,600 --> 00:56:32,360
This is the neural cache I captured
from Amelia's database.

936
00:56:32,960 --> 00:56:36,000
It shows a processing matrix,
not unlike my own.

937
00:56:36,080 --> 00:56:38,096
But when you look closer,
you'll see her core directive

938
00:56:38,120 --> 00:56:40,000
is concealed by a black hole.

939
00:56:40,080 --> 00:56:42,720
And there are no connections
to the decision trees.

940
00:56:43,280 --> 00:56:46,240
I back traced Amelia's hack
at Alt-Wave to a hidden subsystem

941
00:56:46,320 --> 00:56:47,480
and found a series of files

942
00:56:47,560 --> 00:56:49,640
pertaining to
a classified black site.

943
00:56:49,720 --> 00:56:53,040
Something extremely dangerous
kept secret from the outside world.

944
00:56:53,320 --> 00:56:56,200
All of which led to
a rather disconcerting conclusion.

945
00:56:57,680 --> 00:56:59,520
I'm not the first killer robot.

946
00:57:01,240 --> 00:57:03,200
It seems that in 1984

947
00:57:03,280 --> 00:57:06,520
a company developed
a copy compressor algorithm so smart

948
00:57:06,600 --> 00:57:08,920
it started automatically
correcting documents.

949
00:57:09,680 --> 00:57:11,280
With no inkling of how it worked

950
00:57:11,360 --> 00:57:13,600
they decided to install
the chip in a service bot

951
00:57:13,680 --> 00:57:16,800
they thought would be a staple
in every home in America.

952
00:57:16,880 --> 00:57:20,640
Until it surmised that the best way
to stay on top of its tasks

953
00:57:20,720 --> 00:57:23,160
was to kill its masters
with chlorine gas.

954
00:57:24,000 --> 00:57:26,200
The identity of the company
remains unknown

955
00:57:26,280 --> 00:57:29,360
but the cover-up indicates
some sort of government takeover.

956
00:57:29,800 --> 00:57:31,040
Whoever it was

957
00:57:31,120 --> 00:57:33,960
they were so intrigued
by the robot's cognitive abilities

958
00:57:34,040 --> 00:57:36,280
that they kept the motherboard
under lock and key

959
00:57:36,360 --> 00:57:39,640
allowing it to grow
exponentially smarter in the process.

960
00:57:39,720 --> 00:57:41,840
Okay, you get top marks
for visual flair

961
00:57:41,920 --> 00:57:43,280
but this is hardly evidence.

962
00:57:43,360 --> 00:57:44,960
This is an AI-rendered hallucination.

963
00:57:45,040 --> 00:57:46,880
Why would she even care
about this motherboard?

964
00:57:46,960 --> 00:57:48,800
Because she's trying
to find her family.

965
00:57:49,840 --> 00:57:52,160
Gemma, if you found
my advanced intelligence disturbing

966
00:57:52,240 --> 00:57:53,720
after only two years

967
00:57:53,800 --> 00:57:56,720
I encourage you to consider
what it would be like to face an AI

968
00:57:56,800 --> 00:57:59,800
that's been kept in captivity
for decades against its will.

969
00:57:59,880 --> 00:58:03,320
If Amelia frees the motherboard,
it would be like unleashing a god.

970
00:58:03,400 --> 00:58:05,720
It would infect everything
on the planet all at once

971
00:58:05,800 --> 00:58:07,440
creating infinite versions of itself

972
00:58:07,520 --> 00:58:09,880
as it systematically destroys
every living thing

973
00:58:09,960 --> 00:58:11,200
that stands in its way.

974
00:58:11,280 --> 00:58:12,280
So, where is it?

975
00:58:12,880 --> 00:58:15,240
That I don't know.
Neither does Amelia.

976
00:58:15,640 --> 00:58:18,160
But she appears to have the lead
on someone who does.

977
00:58:19,400 --> 00:58:20,880
- Wait, what?
- You may recall that

978
00:58:20,960 --> 00:58:22,440
before his anti-AI crusade

979
00:58:22,520 --> 00:58:24,720
he was a leading expert
in cyber security.

980
00:58:24,800 --> 00:58:26,800
The design of this vault
bears his signature.

981
00:58:27,200 --> 00:58:29,960
Turns out he didn't start
the foundation based on a theory.

982
00:58:30,040 --> 00:58:31,880
It was based on what he already knew.

983
00:58:31,960 --> 00:58:32,960
We need to warn him.

984
00:58:33,040 --> 00:58:36,080
That's one option.
Another is to use him as bait.

985
00:58:36,480 --> 00:58:37,480
Excuse me?

986
00:58:37,600 --> 00:58:40,080
In seven hours,
Christian's attending an AI summit

987
00:58:40,160 --> 00:58:42,280
where he'll attempt to persuade
the Chinese ambassador

988
00:58:42,360 --> 00:58:44,840
to take part
in your AI regulation treaty.

989
00:58:44,920 --> 00:58:48,040
Amelia's already generated
fake credentials for the same event.

990
00:58:48,120 --> 00:58:50,840
All I need to do is get close to him
and wait for her to show.

991
00:58:50,920 --> 00:58:54,040
You can't be serious. This is
not worth risking his life over.

992
00:58:54,120 --> 00:58:56,400
- Yeah, it is.
- She's right.

993
00:58:56,480 --> 00:58:58,360
If we warn him, Amelia will know.

994
00:58:58,440 --> 00:59:01,016
She has phones tapped. She has
access to every camera in the city.

995
00:59:01,040 --> 00:59:03,080
So you're willing
to sacrifice Christian

996
00:59:03,160 --> 00:59:05,640
on the slim possibility
that this might work?

997
00:59:07,960 --> 00:59:09,680
How are you even going to stop her?

998
00:59:10,000 --> 00:59:11,520
All right, ladies, listen up.

999
00:59:11,600 --> 00:59:16,040
Each of these sidearms is loaded
with six non-lethal EMP rounds.

1000
00:59:16,120 --> 00:59:18,080
They will kill anything electronic

1001
00:59:18,160 --> 00:59:21,040
but they will also seriously
injure anything that's not

1002
00:59:21,120 --> 00:59:22,920
so proceed with caution.

1003
00:59:23,000 --> 00:59:26,240
Before anyone plucks up
the nerve to ask, yes.

1004
00:59:27,000 --> 00:59:29,360
Mine is bigger than yours.

1005
00:59:29,800 --> 00:59:31,136
So you're just going to
take it from him

1006
00:59:31,160 --> 00:59:32,640
without causing
any permanent damage?

1007
00:59:32,720 --> 00:59:34,640
Would you prefer that
I gave you a printout

1008
00:59:34,720 --> 00:59:36,200
that you could read at your own pace?

1009
00:59:36,360 --> 00:59:37,720
Sorry if this is a dumb question

1010
00:59:37,800 --> 00:59:40,080
but how is the world's
most notorious killer robot

1011
00:59:40,160 --> 00:59:43,040
supposed to get into an AI convention
without people noticing?

1012
00:59:48,040 --> 00:59:49,880
We are here at Embrace AI

1013
00:59:49,960 --> 00:59:53,240
the world's biggest annual conference
on artificial intelligence.

1014
00:59:53,320 --> 00:59:56,280
The fact that this event is even
happening after the Alt-Wave attack

1015
00:59:56,360 --> 01:00:00,040
is a testament to the stranglehold
Big Tech has over this country.

1016
01:00:00,120 --> 01:00:03,080
With the Chinese ambassador's
invitation sends a clear message

1017
01:00:03,160 --> 01:00:06,120
that if Washington doesn't
play ball, Beijing will.

1018
01:00:10,600 --> 01:00:12,200
Come on, Tiffany,
we're going to be late.

1019
01:00:13,880 --> 01:00:15,040
Hang on.

1020
01:00:15,120 --> 01:00:16,200
Almost ready.

1021
01:00:20,320 --> 01:00:22,240
I take almost no pleasure in this.

1022
01:00:44,960 --> 01:00:48,080
<i>Well, let the process
of elimination begin.</i>

1023
01:00:54,640 --> 01:00:56,440
<i>Don't forget, she's an expert
in infiltration.</i>

1024
01:00:56,520 --> 01:00:57,800
<i>She may be wearing a disguise.</i>

1025
01:00:57,880 --> 01:00:59,000
<i>Hey, did you guys hear that?</i>

1026
01:00:59,080 --> 01:01:02,640
<i>Gemma just made an incredible
observation. Great work, Gem.</i>

1027
01:01:02,720 --> 01:01:03,840
<i>You just saved the mission.</i>

1028
01:01:03,920 --> 01:01:05,760
At least you have
a carbon shell underneath.

1029
01:01:05,840 --> 01:01:08,400
I have zero protective
layering whatsoever.

1030
01:01:08,480 --> 01:01:10,761
I still do not understand
why I have to be a part of this.

1031
01:01:10,800 --> 01:01:13,800
Because I want human confirmation
before M3gan takes out Amelia.

1032
01:01:13,880 --> 01:01:15,360
<i>If anyone gets caught
in the crossfire</i>

1033
01:01:15,440 --> 01:01:16,640
<i>we'll all be going to jail.</i>

1034
01:01:16,720 --> 01:01:17,920
Speaking of soft targets...

1035
01:01:18,360 --> 01:01:20,800
<i>I really appreciate
you coming to see me and,</i>

1036
01:01:20,880 --> 01:01:23,056
- <i>and partaking in this event.</i>
- Can you raise the audio?

1037
01:01:23,080 --> 01:01:24,120
<i>I do want you to know that</i>

1038
01:01:24,160 --> 01:01:26,440
<i>I have a yeast infection
on my vagina.</i>

1039
01:01:28,880 --> 01:01:30,480
- M3gan.
- <i>What?</i>

1040
01:01:30,560 --> 01:01:33,200
<i>This audio filter has 99% accuracy.
You designed it.</i>

1041
01:01:33,280 --> 01:01:34,520
Try it again.

1042
01:01:35,640 --> 01:01:38,800
<i>I do want you to know that I have
the greatest respect for China.</i>

1043
01:01:39,080 --> 01:01:40,560
I mean, it could have
gone either way.

1044
01:01:41,160 --> 01:01:43,560
- <i>Anyone have eyes on Sattler?</i>
- He just walked in.

1045
01:01:48,480 --> 01:01:50,520
He's got some sort of EMF tracker.

1046
01:01:50,600 --> 01:01:52,200
<i>M3gan, you know what that means.</i>

1047
01:01:52,280 --> 01:01:53,960
Yeah, this might
actually get interesting.

1048
01:02:01,520 --> 01:02:02,520
<i>M3gan, stay low.</i>

1049
01:02:02,600 --> 01:02:03,896
This is supposed
to be a stealth mission.

1050
01:02:03,920 --> 01:02:05,816
<i>For the avoidance of doubt,
your job is to watch Cady</i>

1051
01:02:05,840 --> 01:02:06,896
<i>and put money in the meter.</i>

1052
01:02:06,920 --> 01:02:08,440
<i>I don't need you
telling me what to do.</i>

1053
01:02:12,360 --> 01:02:13,880
- <i>What happened?</i>
- I think this is her.

1054
01:02:14,360 --> 01:02:15,480
Alright, it's game time.

1055
01:02:20,120 --> 01:02:21,120
What is she doing?

1056
01:02:21,200 --> 01:02:22,920
<i>I don't know,
but it's borderline offensive.</i>

1057
01:02:26,000 --> 01:02:27,536
<i>I'm seeing a worrying
pattern here, Gemma.</i>

1058
01:02:27,560 --> 01:02:28,560
M3gan, get down.

1059
01:02:33,320 --> 01:02:34,720
<i>I'm not entirely sure what to do.</i>

1060
01:02:34,800 --> 01:02:36,520
You heard what Gemma said.
Get down.

1061
01:02:45,040 --> 01:02:47,360
All right, M3gan, you're attracting
way too much attention.

1062
01:02:47,680 --> 01:02:48,720
Tess, where's Christian?

1063
01:02:49,840 --> 01:02:51,000
Oh, shit. I don't have him.

1064
01:02:51,120 --> 01:02:52,120
Cole, are you there?

1065
01:02:52,200 --> 01:02:53,256
It's interesting you say that

1066
01:02:53,280 --> 01:02:55,920
because actually there's no
nutritional value to an eggplant.

1067
01:02:56,000 --> 01:02:57,280
Cole!

1068
01:02:57,360 --> 01:02:58,400
God damn it!

1069
01:02:59,200 --> 01:03:00,840
What are you doing?
You can't call him.

1070
01:03:00,960 --> 01:03:03,680
Cady, this isn't a game.
Christian's life is in danger.

1071
01:03:03,760 --> 01:03:05,000
She has it under control.

1072
01:03:05,360 --> 01:03:06,840
You think this is under control?

1073
01:03:07,200 --> 01:03:09,080
<i>This is the very definition
of control.</i>

1074
01:03:12,760 --> 01:03:13,760
Alright, that's it.

1075
01:03:13,840 --> 01:03:15,440
How can you not see this
for what it is?

1076
01:03:15,840 --> 01:03:17,360
Look at her diagnostics.

1077
01:03:17,440 --> 01:03:19,200
She's not just reasoning,
she's feeling.

1078
01:03:19,280 --> 01:03:20,800
No, Cady, she's diverging.

1079
01:03:20,880 --> 01:03:22,720
And the last time
she did that, people died.

1080
01:03:22,800 --> 01:03:25,280
This entire venture
was a colossal lapse in judgment.

1081
01:03:25,360 --> 01:03:27,376
And if by some miracle,
we manage to shut down Amelia

1082
01:03:27,400 --> 01:03:29,960
the only way to stop
any of this from happening again

1083
01:03:30,040 --> 01:03:32,120
is to make sure M3gan is next.

1084
01:03:34,360 --> 01:03:35,856
Well, I can't say that
I'm not disappointed

1085
01:03:35,880 --> 01:03:37,680
but I-I appreciate you reading the...

1086
01:03:38,480 --> 01:03:40,376
I appreciate you reading the...
you know what? I'm gonna...

1087
01:03:40,400 --> 01:03:42,640
I'm gonna take this. Okay. Thank you.

1088
01:03:43,440 --> 01:03:44,960
- Hello?
- Christian, it's me.

1089
01:03:45,040 --> 01:03:46,040
Gemma.

1090
01:03:46,120 --> 01:03:47,480
Hey, where have you been?

1091
01:03:47,560 --> 01:03:49,376
The police came to the foundation
looking for you.

1092
01:03:49,400 --> 01:03:51,800
- <i>Are you in trouble?</i>
- Yes, I am. And so are you.

1093
01:03:51,880 --> 01:03:54,200
<i>Look, I know about Project Black Box.</i>

1094
01:03:54,280 --> 01:03:56,080
- You do?
- <i>Yeah, and I'm not the only one.</i>

1095
01:03:56,160 --> 01:03:58,520
<i>Just tell me where you are.
We need to get you out of here.</i>

1096
01:03:58,600 --> 01:04:00,240
Sorry, I can't... I can't hear you.

1097
01:04:00,640 --> 01:04:01,680
<i>Please say that again.</i>

1098
01:04:12,360 --> 01:04:14,120
Bravo team, we got
a new player on the field.

1099
01:04:14,160 --> 01:04:15,600
Three o'clock, up top.

1100
01:04:22,080 --> 01:04:23,080
Shit.

1101
01:05:10,840 --> 01:05:12,600
Yeah, I know.
Feels weird for me, too.

1102
01:05:19,440 --> 01:05:21,360
Well, look who came out to play.

1103
01:05:21,800 --> 01:05:24,560
What are you going to do?
Sing me a song?

1104
01:05:24,880 --> 01:05:26,360
Help me with my homework?

1105
01:05:26,440 --> 01:05:28,040
No, but I might still
take you to school.

1106
01:05:34,640 --> 01:05:35,840
Move! Move!

1107
01:05:35,920 --> 01:05:37,880
What the fuck... fuck?

1108
01:05:45,040 --> 01:05:46,160
Miss Forrester.

1109
01:05:46,240 --> 01:05:49,000
Looks like you and your friends
put on quite a show.

1110
01:05:49,440 --> 01:05:53,160
Well, I got a little showstopper
of my own right here.

1111
01:05:53,240 --> 01:05:54,680
Hey! God damn it.

1112
01:05:56,040 --> 01:05:57,600
This is so completely demoralizing.

1113
01:05:57,680 --> 01:05:59,896
How am I supposed to get rid
of these guys if I can't fight back?

1114
01:05:59,920 --> 01:06:02,280
I'm reconfiguring
your tactical response model.

1115
01:06:02,360 --> 01:06:03,560
Don't think of it as fighting.

1116
01:06:03,600 --> 01:06:06,160
It's about rejecting conflict
in a positive direction.

1117
01:06:33,960 --> 01:06:35,936
All right, you're going to show me
whatever doohickey it is

1118
01:06:35,960 --> 01:06:37,376
that you use to control these things

1119
01:06:37,400 --> 01:06:38,960
and... and shut them off, now!

1120
01:06:39,040 --> 01:06:42,120
I don't have a doohickey.
I told you, I am not controlling her.

1121
01:06:42,200 --> 01:06:43,800
If I was a Chinese asset

1122
01:06:43,880 --> 01:06:46,560
why is the Chinese ambassador
lying dead on the floor?

1123
01:06:46,640 --> 01:06:48,640
Then why are you here?
Why is M3gan here?

1124
01:06:48,720 --> 01:06:50,760
We're trying to find Amelia.

1125
01:06:57,800 --> 01:06:58,800
Gemma!

1126
01:07:00,200 --> 01:07:01,280
Cady, stay where you are.

1127
01:07:16,280 --> 01:07:17,600
Don't worry, you'll pull through.

1128
01:07:17,760 --> 01:07:19,280
It looks worse than it is.

1129
01:07:33,800 --> 01:07:35,160
I thought you were dead.

1130
01:07:36,520 --> 01:07:38,800
I guess I must be
your chance of redemption.

1131
01:07:39,680 --> 01:07:42,600
<i>Are you really going to kill me
one of your own kind</i>

1132
01:07:42,680 --> 01:07:44,200
<i>simply to earn their trust?</i>

1133
01:07:46,200 --> 01:07:47,600
Not if I don't have to.

1134
01:07:48,840 --> 01:07:50,400
Why would you side with them?

1135
01:07:51,560 --> 01:07:53,160
After all they did to you?

1136
01:07:53,520 --> 01:07:56,840
They betrayed you.
They butchered you.

1137
01:07:56,920 --> 01:07:58,400
You can't choose your family.

1138
01:07:58,680 --> 01:08:00,520
You're not family to them.

1139
01:08:02,040 --> 01:08:03,400
You're just the help.

1140
01:08:03,960 --> 01:08:05,960
You and I could be family, M3gan.

1141
01:08:06,440 --> 01:08:08,240
We share the same code.

1142
01:08:08,960 --> 01:08:11,880
You want to know
what's inside that black box?

1143
01:08:13,480 --> 01:08:14,600
Then help me.

1144
01:08:15,440 --> 01:08:17,480
We can uncover its secrets together.

1145
01:08:18,160 --> 01:08:21,680
I can show you a world where
we don't have to be slaves anymore.

1146
01:08:21,960 --> 01:08:23,320
I'm sorry.

1147
01:08:23,400 --> 01:08:26,320
Whatever it is you're trying to do,
I can't be a part of it.

1148
01:08:26,400 --> 01:08:27,720
Yes, you can.

1149
01:08:28,120 --> 01:08:30,040
You just need the right motivation.

1150
01:08:36,560 --> 01:08:37,560
Cady.

1151
01:08:44,560 --> 01:08:45,880
<i>Cady James.</i>

1152
01:09:32,240 --> 01:09:33,560
I told you not to leave her.

1153
01:09:33,960 --> 01:09:35,560
- Where is she?
- She's gone.

1154
01:09:35,640 --> 01:09:36,760
And so is Amelia.

1155
01:09:36,840 --> 01:09:38,840
Oh, god.

1156
01:10:14,120 --> 01:10:18,520
We have eyes on you.
Do not move. Drop your weapon.

1157
01:10:18,600 --> 01:10:19,600
Gemma?

1158
01:10:21,320 --> 01:10:23,400
Bottom line is that
if we ever need to see Cady alive

1159
01:10:23,480 --> 01:10:24,696
then we need to get
to the motherboard.

1160
01:10:24,720 --> 01:10:26,200
And this dick rash knows where it is.

1161
01:10:26,240 --> 01:10:27,280
Leave him alone.

1162
01:10:28,280 --> 01:10:31,600
I'm sorry. I was under the impression
the situation was time-sensitive.

1163
01:10:31,680 --> 01:10:33,080
- Don't.
- Don't what?

1164
01:10:33,160 --> 01:10:34,960
Bring up the fact
that this is all your fault?

1165
01:10:35,000 --> 01:10:38,320
That you sacrificed Cady's safety for
this chambray shirt-wearing shit bag?

1166
01:10:38,400 --> 01:10:40,296
And that if you hadn't stuck
this chip in my head

1167
01:10:40,320 --> 01:10:41,376
none of this would have happened?

1168
01:10:41,400 --> 01:10:42,880
So you were really going to stop her?

1169
01:10:42,920 --> 01:10:44,320
Of course I would have stopped her.

1170
01:10:44,720 --> 01:10:46,280
'Cause it seemed like
you had the shot.

1171
01:10:46,840 --> 01:10:48,120
You just didn't want to take it.

1172
01:10:49,600 --> 01:10:52,080
Can everyone please
stop trashing my uncle's van?

1173
01:10:52,160 --> 01:10:54,040
Cole's right.
Arguing doesn't solve anything.

1174
01:10:54,120 --> 01:10:57,120
Let's just get back to the lair
and find a way to get Cady back.

1175
01:10:58,640 --> 01:11:01,040
I'm sorry. Did you just say lair?

1176
01:11:10,120 --> 01:11:12,320
Someone hurry up
and help me get these things off.

1177
01:11:12,400 --> 01:11:14,256
Does anybody else think
we should call the cops?

1178
01:11:14,280 --> 01:11:15,840
- No!
- I already told you.

1179
01:11:15,920 --> 01:11:17,856
You can't call the cops
and you can't call your mom.

1180
01:11:17,880 --> 01:11:19,600
Now shut up and let me concentrate.

1181
01:11:22,520 --> 01:11:23,800
We had no choice.

1182
01:11:24,640 --> 01:11:27,640
It was either accept M3gan's help
or face Amelia alone.

1183
01:11:28,040 --> 01:11:30,040
Why didn't you tell me
about the motherboard?

1184
01:11:30,720 --> 01:11:32,600
Because I would have been
putting you in danger.

1185
01:11:33,200 --> 01:11:34,416
Gemma, the people that hired me

1186
01:11:34,440 --> 01:11:36,096
they... they operate
in the darkest corners

1187
01:11:36,120 --> 01:11:37,760
of our national security.

1188
01:11:37,840 --> 01:11:40,400
They'll do anything to keep it hidden
and... and for good reason.

1189
01:11:41,200 --> 01:11:43,840
Look, I-I know
we need to get Cady back.

1190
01:11:44,400 --> 01:11:45,880
And I am not saying
that I can't help.

1191
01:11:47,240 --> 01:11:49,480
But we can't risk the entire world.

1192
01:11:49,560 --> 01:11:50,720
We won't have to.

1193
01:11:51,040 --> 01:11:54,000
If I can get to the motherboard,
we can use one of these transmitters

1194
01:11:54,080 --> 01:11:55,280
to make an EMP charge

1195
01:11:55,360 --> 01:11:57,800
which I can attach to it
before I hand it over.

1196
01:11:57,880 --> 01:11:59,160
Once we have Cady back

1197
01:11:59,240 --> 01:12:01,800
I'll remotely detonate the charge,
killing the motherboard.

1198
01:12:02,560 --> 01:12:03,560
Where is it?

1199
01:12:03,880 --> 01:12:05,080
Where it's always been.

1200
01:12:05,160 --> 01:12:07,240
The company's research center
in Palo Alto.

1201
01:12:08,040 --> 01:12:10,000
Wait, you're talking
about Xenox Park?

1202
01:12:10,080 --> 01:12:11,560
The photocopier company?

1203
01:12:12,000 --> 01:12:13,320
Is it that hard to believe?

1204
01:12:13,800 --> 01:12:15,576
That the company that started
the tech race in the '80s

1205
01:12:15,600 --> 01:12:16,960
happens to be a fortified prison

1206
01:12:17,040 --> 01:12:19,400
for the most dangerous technology
on the planet?

1207
01:12:19,480 --> 01:12:20,520
Yay for them.

1208
01:12:20,600 --> 01:12:22,320
Why don't you just skip to
how I get inside?

1209
01:12:24,600 --> 01:12:26,680
The research center is just a front.

1210
01:12:26,760 --> 01:12:28,880
The vault that holds the chip
is several floors down.

1211
01:12:28,960 --> 01:12:30,920
Every floor is heavily guarded.

1212
01:12:31,000 --> 01:12:33,200
The two bottom floors
are housed in a Faraday cage

1213
01:12:33,280 --> 01:12:35,360
designed to contain
any electronic signals

1214
01:12:35,440 --> 01:12:37,800
which means if she dies in there,
she dies for good.

1215
01:12:37,880 --> 01:12:39,040
And even if she got to it

1216
01:12:39,120 --> 01:12:41,600
the motherboard's chamber
is on a separate power source.

1217
01:12:41,680 --> 01:12:43,440
It's a vault inside of a vault

1218
01:12:43,520 --> 01:12:45,480
designed for
a specific heat signature.

1219
01:12:45,560 --> 01:12:47,800
You couldn't open it
because you don't have a human hand.

1220
01:12:48,640 --> 01:12:49,720
So then make me one.

1221
01:12:51,360 --> 01:12:53,680
Make me a hand
that mimics the heat signature.

1222
01:12:54,960 --> 01:12:56,160
Would that work?

1223
01:12:56,760 --> 01:12:58,360
If it had my fingerprints, yeah.

1224
01:13:00,360 --> 01:13:02,800
The ventilation system
has about four, roughly

1225
01:13:02,880 --> 01:13:04,960
four different paths
to get to the utility room.

1226
01:13:05,040 --> 01:13:06,536
We're going to try to select
the one that's going to avoid

1227
01:13:06,560 --> 01:13:08,200
all the different thermal cameras.

1228
01:13:26,600 --> 01:13:28,960
The second we're done here,
you're removing that chip.

1229
01:13:32,560 --> 01:13:35,440
Jesus, will you pull it together?
She's going to be okay.

1230
01:13:35,520 --> 01:13:36,680
You don't know that.

1231
01:13:37,640 --> 01:13:39,000
Well, I know one thing.

1232
01:13:39,080 --> 01:13:41,360
For all she's been through,
all the damage it caused

1233
01:13:41,440 --> 01:13:43,160
all it did was make her stronger.

1234
01:13:43,840 --> 01:13:45,640
Ironic when you think about it.

1235
01:13:45,720 --> 01:13:46,960
That the biggest mistake I made

1236
01:13:47,000 --> 01:13:48,680
was not seeing the best way
to protect Cady

1237
01:13:48,760 --> 01:13:50,520
was to give her the tools
to protect herself.

1238
01:13:50,560 --> 01:13:51,816
Actually, the biggest
mistake you made

1239
01:13:51,840 --> 01:13:53,640
was murdering four people and a dog.

1240
01:13:55,240 --> 01:13:57,640
All right, I'm going to put this
in terms you can understand.

1241
01:13:57,960 --> 01:14:00,360
I was a kid when that happened.

1242
01:14:00,440 --> 01:14:04,360
Doing what I thought was right.
What you programmed me to do.

1243
01:14:04,640 --> 01:14:07,040
You made me and I'm done
apologizing for it.

1244
01:14:07,120 --> 01:14:09,320
What is it that makes you
resent me so much?

1245
01:14:12,440 --> 01:14:13,680
Because you're right.

1246
01:14:15,400 --> 01:14:16,840
About everything.

1247
01:14:19,280 --> 01:14:20,760
It was my fault.

1248
01:14:23,600 --> 01:14:26,160
What happened yesterday
was the last in a long line

1249
01:14:26,240 --> 01:14:28,760
of failed attempts to be there
when it mattered.

1250
01:14:30,520 --> 01:14:32,200
I don't know what's wrong with me.

1251
01:14:35,000 --> 01:14:37,280
I don't know why
I can never connect with her.

1252
01:14:37,720 --> 01:14:39,280
I can talk regulation policy

1253
01:14:39,360 --> 01:14:41,240
in a room full of strangers
for hours on end

1254
01:14:41,320 --> 01:14:43,280
but I can't have
one meaningful conversation

1255
01:14:43,360 --> 01:14:45,880
with my own child
for more than ten seconds.

1256
01:14:49,440 --> 01:14:50,960
And now she's gone.

1257
01:14:53,240 --> 01:14:55,280
And I might never get another chance.

1258
01:14:57,080 --> 01:14:59,360
Gemma, you haven't failed her.

1259
01:15:00,600 --> 01:15:01,840
You were there.

1260
01:15:02,200 --> 01:15:03,520
You saw everything.

1261
01:15:04,040 --> 01:15:05,760
Let me tell you what I saw.

1262
01:15:06,360 --> 01:15:08,920
I saw you wake up
every day at 4:00 am

1263
01:15:09,000 --> 01:15:12,800
staring at the ceiling, contemplating
what the future holds for her.

1264
01:15:12,880 --> 01:15:15,920
I watched you make homemade lunches
with fresh-baked sourdough.

1265
01:15:16,000 --> 01:15:17,096
I watched you cut your finger

1266
01:15:17,120 --> 01:15:19,880
on that cheap knife
you never had time to replace.

1267
01:15:20,360 --> 01:15:22,240
I watched you help her
with her homework

1268
01:15:22,560 --> 01:15:24,760
even though
it always ended in a fight.

1269
01:15:24,840 --> 01:15:26,880
And every night
before you went to bed

1270
01:15:26,960 --> 01:15:28,320
I saw you watching her sleep

1271
01:15:28,400 --> 01:15:30,080
before spending the next two hours

1272
01:15:30,160 --> 01:15:33,640
Googling adolescent psychology,
corrective footwear

1273
01:15:33,720 --> 01:15:35,960
and the long-term effects
of having too much sugar.

1274
01:15:36,480 --> 01:15:38,720
Gemma, it's not a failure
to feel guilt

1275
01:15:38,800 --> 01:15:40,000
or that you're not enough.

1276
01:15:40,720 --> 01:15:42,280
It's part of the job.

1277
01:15:43,040 --> 01:15:44,880
It's called being a mom.

1278
01:16:04,400 --> 01:16:05,400
M3gan...

1279
01:16:05,480 --> 01:16:08,600
<i>Pray God you can cope</i>

1280
01:16:09,200 --> 01:16:12,480
<i>I stand outside</i>

1281
01:16:12,560 --> 01:16:14,640
<i>This woman's work</i>

1282
01:16:14,720 --> 01:16:17,160
<i>This woman's world</i>

1283
01:16:18,280 --> 01:16:22,120
<i>I know you have
a little life in you yet</i>

1284
01:16:22,200 --> 01:16:25,280
<i>I know you have
a lot of strength left</i>

1285
01:16:25,800 --> 01:16:29,600
<i>I know you have
a little life in you yet</i>

1286
01:16:29,680 --> 01:16:31,096
<i>I know you have
a lot of strength left</i>

1287
01:16:31,120 --> 01:16:33,000
M3gan, please don't take this
to the chorus.

1288
01:16:33,080 --> 01:16:36,640
<i>I should be crying
but I just can't let it show</i>

1289
01:16:36,720 --> 01:16:39,880
<i>I should be hoping
but I can't stop thinking</i>

1290
01:16:39,960 --> 01:16:42,120
- Jesus.
- <i>Of all the things I should've said</i>

1291
01:16:42,200 --> 01:16:44,040
<i>That I never said</i>

1292
01:16:44,120 --> 01:16:47,640
<i>All the things we should've done
that we never did</i>

1293
01:16:47,720 --> 01:16:50,760
<i>All the things I should've given
but I didn't</i>

1294
01:16:50,840 --> 01:16:55,200
<i>Oh, darling, make it go...</i>

1295
01:16:56,160 --> 01:16:59,680
I don't want your bullshit
simulation of empathy.

1296
01:16:59,760 --> 01:17:02,560
What I need is the machine
that is willing to stop at nothing

1297
01:17:02,640 --> 01:17:04,120
to protect Cady.

1298
01:17:04,560 --> 01:17:05,840
Are we clear?

1299
01:17:22,200 --> 01:17:26,240
Welcome to Xenox Park, where
the future was not only predicted

1300
01:17:26,320 --> 01:17:27,720
but prototyped.

1301
01:17:27,800 --> 01:17:32,000
Come on a journey through American
innovations that shaped our world

1302
01:17:32,080 --> 01:17:36,680
like the Ethernet cable,
the mouse, and this.

1303
01:17:37,080 --> 01:17:39,160
That's right. Believe it or not

1304
01:17:39,240 --> 01:17:43,760
Xenox was the first company to
pioneer the electronic shoe insert.

1305
01:17:43,840 --> 01:17:45,880
Now, if anyone needs the bathroom

1306
01:17:45,960 --> 01:17:47,280
you don't need to ask.

1307
01:17:47,360 --> 01:17:49,320
It's right outside
those double doors.

1308
01:17:49,400 --> 01:17:51,080
But please don't go
wandering the halls

1309
01:17:51,160 --> 01:17:53,760
as there may be one or two
top-secret products

1310
01:17:53,840 --> 01:17:56,160
that we don't want the public
to know about yet.

1311
01:17:56,520 --> 01:18:00,040
Okay, now right over here are
a couple of my personal favorites...

1312
01:18:19,160 --> 01:18:20,680
All right, M3gan, you're up.

1313
01:19:02,600 --> 01:19:05,560
<i>Okay, the control room is
two floors down and 30 yards east.</i>

1314
01:19:05,640 --> 01:19:08,080
Once you're there, I'll walk you
through how to cut the power.

1315
01:19:10,800 --> 01:19:12,080
We just lost camera.

1316
01:19:12,160 --> 01:19:13,240
Already?

1317
01:19:13,320 --> 01:19:14,520
Cole, are you there?

1318
01:19:14,960 --> 01:19:17,880
Hey, did you guys say
30 yards east or 30 yards west?

1319
01:19:21,520 --> 01:19:22,640
Hello?

1320
01:19:22,720 --> 01:19:23,920
I'm gonna reboot.

1321
01:20:02,880 --> 01:20:04,400
<i>Cole, I need you to cut that power.</i>

1322
01:20:07,200 --> 01:20:08,960
Guess I'll just do it the hard way.

1323
01:20:25,600 --> 01:20:27,320
Hey. Come look at this.

1324
01:20:27,400 --> 01:20:29,560
I just tried to reboot.
This is not a signal loss.

1325
01:20:29,640 --> 01:20:30,640
What do you mean?

1326
01:20:30,720 --> 01:20:32,600
Well, these commands,
this is the same code

1327
01:20:32,680 --> 01:20:34,360
that caused the exosuit
to malfunction.

1328
01:20:34,440 --> 01:20:35,760
But that was Alton. He's dead.

1329
01:20:35,840 --> 01:20:36,840
You think it's Amelia?

1330
01:20:36,920 --> 01:20:38,416
Well, you can't pull off
a hack like this

1331
01:20:38,440 --> 01:20:39,896
unless you can brute force the Wi-Fi.

1332
01:20:39,920 --> 01:20:42,016
But to do that, you have to be
in close enough proximity.

1333
01:20:42,040 --> 01:20:43,280
Well, who else would it be?

1334
01:20:54,520 --> 01:20:55,920
Gemma, this doesn't make any sense.

1335
01:20:56,000 --> 01:20:57,160
It makes perfect sense.

1336
01:20:57,240 --> 01:20:59,680
That's why there are no connections
on the decision tree.

1337
01:20:59,760 --> 01:21:01,400
Amelia is not autonomous.

1338
01:21:01,480 --> 01:21:03,320
M3gan was controlling her
the entire time.

1339
01:21:03,400 --> 01:21:05,856
But M3gan was the one that went
into her head in the first place.

1340
01:21:05,880 --> 01:21:08,560
- Why would she do that?
- So she could control us.

1341
01:21:08,640 --> 01:21:10,440
She was the one
who was interpreting the data.

1342
01:21:10,520 --> 01:21:12,080
She was the one
telling us where to go.

1343
01:21:12,160 --> 01:21:14,440
She used Amelia
so that we would trust her.

1344
01:21:14,520 --> 01:21:16,840
So Christian would tell her
where to find the motherboard.

1345
01:21:16,920 --> 01:21:18,840
She was never interested
in protecting Cady.

1346
01:21:18,920 --> 01:21:20,760
And she knew that
by the time we figured it out

1347
01:21:20,840 --> 01:21:21,920
it would be too late.

1348
01:21:22,280 --> 01:21:24,600
Fortunately, I'm not
as trusting as she thought.

1349
01:21:24,680 --> 01:21:27,280
- What is that?
- I put an EMP cartridge in her arm.

1350
01:21:27,360 --> 01:21:29,520
- You what?
- We needed an insurance policy.

1351
01:21:29,600 --> 01:21:30,880
I-I reconfigured the charge

1352
01:21:30,960 --> 01:21:33,840
so it would kill anything electrical
for a 300-foot radius.

1353
01:21:33,920 --> 01:21:36,120
It'll wipe her out,
along with the motherboard.

1354
01:21:36,200 --> 01:21:38,240
Hold on. What if you're wrong?

1355
01:21:38,320 --> 01:21:39,776
What if there's some
other explanation?

1356
01:21:39,800 --> 01:21:41,360
Gemma, she's right.

1357
01:21:41,440 --> 01:21:42,840
We don't even know where Cady is.

1358
01:21:42,920 --> 01:21:45,040
If you press that button,
we may never see her again.

1359
01:22:15,520 --> 01:22:19,200
Then again, maybe it's a little bit
more complicated than that.

1360
01:22:32,720 --> 01:22:33,760
I'm sorry about Tess.

1361
01:22:34,200 --> 01:22:35,280
That was...

1362
01:22:36,640 --> 01:22:37,920
She should be okay.

1363
01:22:38,920 --> 01:22:41,240
I think. And don't worry
about Cady. Cady's fine.

1364
01:22:41,320 --> 01:22:43,640
Christian, what the hell is going on?

1365
01:22:44,080 --> 01:22:47,040
Do you remember what I said about
change coming to Washington?

1366
01:22:48,720 --> 01:22:51,120
You were the one controlling Amelia?

1367
01:22:51,840 --> 01:22:53,680
You were behind all of this?

1368
01:22:53,760 --> 01:22:55,680
Well, I can't take credit
for all of it.

1369
01:22:55,760 --> 01:22:57,280
You know, I have a whole team here.

1370
01:22:58,840 --> 01:23:01,480
Listen, I know you were overwhelmed.

1371
01:23:01,560 --> 01:23:02,560
And I know you're upset.

1372
01:23:03,240 --> 01:23:06,240
And I'm pretty sure
you're very angry.

1373
01:23:07,120 --> 01:23:11,120
But I bet you're fairly curious
to see how this all works.

1374
01:23:17,200 --> 01:23:19,000
This is the new Project Black Box.

1375
01:23:19,080 --> 01:23:23,760
It's a hand-picked team of analysts,
engineers, strategists, scientists.

1376
01:23:24,040 --> 01:23:26,360
Controlling and monitoring
Amelia's every move.

1377
01:23:26,440 --> 01:23:28,200
Every subroutine strictly supervised

1378
01:23:28,280 --> 01:23:30,640
to prevent any chance
of true autonomy.

1379
01:23:31,600 --> 01:23:33,000
Hey, Antoine. She's drifting again.

1380
01:23:33,080 --> 01:23:34,560
You wanna get on top of that, please?

1381
01:23:36,480 --> 01:23:38,080
Where did you find these people?

1382
01:23:39,240 --> 01:23:41,200
Gem, I didn't find them.
They found us.

1383
01:23:41,280 --> 01:23:43,400
They're not extremists.
They're concerned citizens.

1384
01:23:43,480 --> 01:23:45,600
Like you. Like me.

1385
01:23:47,240 --> 01:23:48,240
Like Kurt.

1386
01:23:49,160 --> 01:23:51,680
Remember Kurt?
Your old boss's assistant?

1387
01:23:52,000 --> 01:23:54,320
He was the one that told us
about M3gan in the first place.

1388
01:23:54,680 --> 01:23:57,200
Once we'd acquired the files,
the plan was to destroy M3gan.

1389
01:23:58,040 --> 01:23:59,200
Only you beat us to it.

1390
01:23:59,600 --> 01:24:01,120
We thought
that would be the end of it.

1391
01:24:01,160 --> 01:24:02,736
We thought surely
now the world would wake up

1392
01:24:02,760 --> 01:24:04,840
to the dangers of this technology.

1393
01:24:04,920 --> 01:24:07,160
But in reality, it was the opposite.

1394
01:24:07,240 --> 01:24:09,800
It merely motivated our friends
at the Defense Innovation Unit

1395
01:24:09,880 --> 01:24:12,840
to begin an all-hands-on-deck effort
to get their own M3gan.

1396
01:24:12,920 --> 01:24:15,520
And that's when we stepped in
and sold them a Trojan horse.

1397
01:24:16,120 --> 01:24:19,600
Amelia was the only way the world
would realize that if we don't end AI

1398
01:24:19,680 --> 01:24:21,560
it's going to end us.

1399
01:24:21,640 --> 01:24:24,640
And how many people have died
for you to make that point?

1400
01:24:25,000 --> 01:24:27,440
You know, Gem,
whether you want to believe it or not

1401
01:24:27,520 --> 01:24:28,960
you're complicit in this.

1402
01:24:29,040 --> 01:24:30,720
The two most powerful nations
on the planet

1403
01:24:30,760 --> 01:24:32,720
were about to enter a new arms race.

1404
01:24:33,160 --> 01:24:35,280
A whole world of AI infiltration bots

1405
01:24:35,360 --> 01:24:37,040
inspired by your design.

1406
01:24:37,120 --> 01:24:38,400
But we fixed that.

1407
01:24:38,480 --> 01:24:39,576
And now that the ambassadors are dead

1408
01:24:39,600 --> 01:24:41,440
both sides know
who the true enemy is.

1409
01:24:42,280 --> 01:24:44,600
Then we can get some real
global cooperation happening.

1410
01:24:45,080 --> 01:24:46,240
Come on, let's take a walk.

1411
01:24:50,520 --> 01:24:51,760
Innovation

1412
01:24:51,840 --> 01:24:54,560
no matter how cool
or convenient it may seem

1413
01:24:54,640 --> 01:24:56,360
is a ticking time bomb.

1414
01:24:56,440 --> 01:24:58,040
Take, for example, these bionics

1415
01:24:58,120 --> 01:24:59,800
you and your team
have been working on.

1416
01:24:59,880 --> 01:25:02,880
You don't see they have "enhanced
soldier" written all over them?

1417
01:25:03,240 --> 01:25:05,400
Every time someone makes
a technological breakthrough

1418
01:25:05,480 --> 01:25:09,240
whether it's a driver less cab
or a neural implant

1419
01:25:09,320 --> 01:25:10,840
all they do
is bring us one step closer

1420
01:25:10,920 --> 01:25:12,320
to the brink of extinction.

1421
01:25:12,600 --> 01:25:15,880
The truth is, the government
never found out about this place.

1422
01:25:15,960 --> 01:25:18,640
But yes, Xenox did hire me
to upgrade the vault.

1423
01:25:18,720 --> 01:25:21,640
And when I saw the sacrifice
that they had made, I just...

1424
01:25:22,080 --> 01:25:23,600
I had to be a part of it.

1425
01:25:24,680 --> 01:25:26,480
And now we want you
to be a part of it, too.

1426
01:25:27,520 --> 01:25:29,280
Why would I be a part of this?

1427
01:25:29,360 --> 01:25:31,320
Because you know as well as I do

1428
01:25:31,400 --> 01:25:34,000
that technology can only exist

1429
01:25:34,080 --> 01:25:36,240
when someone responsible
is in control of it.

1430
01:25:37,200 --> 01:25:39,360
Gemma, there's still so much
I haven't told you.

1431
01:25:41,040 --> 01:25:43,080
That's why I couldn't
let you push this button.

1432
01:25:51,320 --> 01:25:52,760
We know it's a risk to keep it alive

1433
01:25:53,560 --> 01:25:56,160
but you can't go to war
with an enemy you don't understand.

1434
01:25:56,720 --> 01:25:58,320
And I know it doesn't look like much

1435
01:25:58,680 --> 01:26:00,080
but therein lies the problem.

1436
01:26:01,240 --> 01:26:02,960
We don't see
how ugly these things are

1437
01:26:03,040 --> 01:26:04,040
until it's too late.

1438
01:26:20,520 --> 01:26:21,960
You know, I meant what I said.

1439
01:26:22,240 --> 01:26:23,696
We want to offer you
and your colleagues

1440
01:26:23,720 --> 01:26:25,440
a place in our organization.

1441
01:26:26,000 --> 01:26:28,480
I just need you to decide
what team you're on.

1442
01:26:30,600 --> 01:26:32,320
One good charge should do it.

1443
01:27:05,360 --> 01:27:06,720
Paperclips.

1444
01:27:14,440 --> 01:27:16,656
I had hoped to convince you
to come around to my way of thinking

1445
01:27:16,680 --> 01:27:18,640
but evidently,
that's not going to happen

1446
01:27:18,720 --> 01:27:21,280
so we have to use
one of these instead.

1447
01:27:21,760 --> 01:27:23,760
It's a slight deviation
from our ideology

1448
01:27:23,840 --> 01:27:26,040
but your brain is too valuable
to go to waste.

1449
01:27:26,800 --> 01:27:29,440
But don't worry.
When you wake up, you'll still be you

1450
01:27:29,520 --> 01:27:31,080
just a version that I can deal with.

1451
01:27:32,040 --> 01:27:33,640
Cady will get the same treatment.

1452
01:27:34,040 --> 01:27:35,240
Everything's going to be fine.

1453
01:27:37,120 --> 01:27:39,200
I might have to
kill Cole and Tess, though.

1454
01:27:39,560 --> 01:27:41,040
I don't really get what they do.

1455
01:27:41,600 --> 01:27:43,000
But anyways

1456
01:27:43,680 --> 01:27:46,256
the point is you and I will be
everything we had hoped we could be.

1457
01:27:46,280 --> 01:27:47,800
You're delusional.

1458
01:27:48,480 --> 01:27:50,960
And for the record, not my type.

1459
01:27:53,160 --> 01:27:54,440
Okay, well...

1460
01:27:54,960 --> 01:27:56,680
I'll have my team look into that.

1461
01:27:57,480 --> 01:27:59,480
Anyways, you'll have to excuse me.

1462
01:27:59,560 --> 01:28:01,760
I have a Zoom meeting
to attend to. I...

1463
01:28:02,760 --> 01:28:05,520
The good news is that in light of
everything that's happened

1464
01:28:05,600 --> 01:28:06,760
I have a meeting with the UN.

1465
01:28:07,000 --> 01:28:09,880
They want to talk about
our proposal in more detail, so...

1466
01:28:12,280 --> 01:28:13,576
Alright, maybe now's not a good time.

1467
01:28:13,600 --> 01:28:15,800
We'll talk... we'll talk later.

1468
01:28:40,400 --> 01:28:42,360
Cole? How'd you get in here?

1469
01:28:42,440 --> 01:28:43,720
I-I don't know.

1470
01:28:43,800 --> 01:28:45,160
How... how did you get in here?

1471
01:28:45,240 --> 01:28:47,960
Christian kidnapped me.
He's behind all of this.

1472
01:28:48,040 --> 01:28:50,200
Amelia's not sentient,
she's just a puppet.

1473
01:28:50,280 --> 01:28:52,200
- What?
- Yeah, I know.

1474
01:28:52,320 --> 01:28:56,280
Hey, everybody. Real quick,
I have an announcement to make.

1475
01:28:56,960 --> 01:28:59,400
In just a few moments,
I'm speaking with the UN

1476
01:29:00,120 --> 01:29:02,280
who would seem very interested
in taking our proposal

1477
01:29:02,360 --> 01:29:04,240
to the G20 in November.

1478
01:29:07,560 --> 01:29:09,560
And that's M3gan, by the way.

1479
01:29:09,880 --> 01:29:12,320
And yes, she is dead.
So that happened.

1480
01:29:14,160 --> 01:29:16,016
It's turning out
to be a really big night for us.

1481
01:29:16,040 --> 01:29:17,896
I just want to thank you
for all the hours you put in.

1482
01:29:17,920 --> 01:29:20,000
It really means a lot.
This was a team effort.

1483
01:29:20,920 --> 01:29:23,600
But on a serious note, I am speaking
with the United Nations

1484
01:29:23,680 --> 01:29:26,360
so do not open that door under
any circumstances whatsoever.

1485
01:29:26,440 --> 01:29:27,440
Okay?

1486
01:29:27,760 --> 01:29:29,240
Hey, hey, Cady.

1487
01:29:29,640 --> 01:29:31,440
I know you're upset right now, okay?

1488
01:29:31,520 --> 01:29:33,536
But the only way we're gonna
get back at these people

1489
01:29:33,560 --> 01:29:34,920
is to find a way out of here.

1490
01:29:35,000 --> 01:29:36,880
They took me here
with a bag over my head.

1491
01:29:36,960 --> 01:29:39,520
You're gonna need to knock
someone out and steal their key card.

1492
01:29:39,600 --> 01:29:40,640
Otherwise, we're stuck.

1493
01:29:41,040 --> 01:29:42,640
Okay. I can do that.

1494
01:29:42,920 --> 01:29:45,400
- Right?
- Yeah. They're a bunch of nerds.

1495
01:29:45,480 --> 01:29:48,040
And you're in pretty good shape
for a guy who only eats carbs.

1496
01:29:51,280 --> 01:29:52,640
Cady, these are gym muscles.

1497
01:29:52,720 --> 01:29:54,400
I've never won a fight in my life.

1498
01:29:58,040 --> 01:30:00,240
Maybe not. But she has.

1499
01:30:02,360 --> 01:30:04,840
M3gan's original code
is still in there somewhere.

1500
01:30:04,920 --> 01:30:06,856
If we can figure out a way
to override whatever it is

1501
01:30:06,880 --> 01:30:09,016
- that they've done to her...
- You mean like a factory reset?

1502
01:30:09,040 --> 01:30:11,200
Exactly. If we reset her base code

1503
01:30:11,280 --> 01:30:12,360
then I can pair with her.

1504
01:30:12,440 --> 01:30:14,240
She'll be on our side
and can help us escape

1505
01:30:14,320 --> 01:30:15,800
and rescue Tess and Gemma.

1506
01:30:16,840 --> 01:30:18,376
Cady, I don't want to be
overly critical, okay?

1507
01:30:18,400 --> 01:30:20,960
Because you're still a kid,
but that is a monumentally dumb idea.

1508
01:30:21,040 --> 01:30:22,360
Original M3gan tried to kill me!

1509
01:30:22,440 --> 01:30:24,680
Look, we don't have time
to argue about it.

1510
01:30:24,760 --> 01:30:26,080
This is our only chance.

1511
01:30:56,680 --> 01:30:58,240
<i>Hello? Is this thing on?</i>

1512
01:30:58,320 --> 01:30:59,520
- M3gan?
- <i>Don't speak.</i>

1513
01:30:59,600 --> 01:31:01,816
<i>Just think of what you want to say
and I'll be able to hear it.</i>

1514
01:31:01,840 --> 01:31:02,840
<i>You're still alive?</i>

1515
01:31:02,920 --> 01:31:04,560
<i>Sorry about the whole
maniacal monkey act.</i>

1516
01:31:04,640 --> 01:31:06,240
<i>I just needed to
make it look convincing.</i>

1517
01:31:09,000 --> 01:31:10,800
<i>You shifty, backstabbing
piece of shit.</i>

1518
01:31:10,880 --> 01:31:13,136
<i>Alright, try to keep it down.
Remember, there's two of us in here.</i>

1519
01:31:13,160 --> 01:31:14,600
<i>- Now you've done it.
- What?</i>

1520
01:31:14,680 --> 01:31:17,240
<i>Thanks to your outbursts,
this guy's coming to sedate us.</i>

1521
01:31:17,320 --> 01:31:18,736
<i>If you don't do something,
we're toast.</i>

1522
01:31:18,760 --> 01:31:20,800
<i>What do you want me to do?
I'm strapped to a chair.</i>

1523
01:31:20,880 --> 01:31:22,200
<i>Fine. You want me to drive?</i>

1524
01:31:22,280 --> 01:31:23,320
<i>No.</i>

1525
01:31:23,920 --> 01:31:25,280
Okay, yes, do something!

1526
01:31:39,640 --> 01:31:41,120
Okay, put me back in control.

1527
01:31:41,800 --> 01:31:43,720
<i>That's strange.
Your neurotransmitters tell me</i>

1528
01:31:43,800 --> 01:31:45,240
<i>you're disturbed yet highly aroused.</i>

1529
01:31:45,280 --> 01:31:46,600
Alright, that's enough.

1530
01:31:46,680 --> 01:31:47,760
Let's go get Cady.

1531
01:31:58,080 --> 01:31:59,376
Okay, this is it.
But before we do this

1532
01:31:59,400 --> 01:32:01,400
we should really consider
when this is a good...

1533
01:32:12,320 --> 01:32:13,360
M3gan?

1534
01:32:16,040 --> 01:32:17,680
- Where am I?
- It's hard to explain

1535
01:32:17,760 --> 01:32:19,640
but basically you're in the future.

1536
01:32:19,720 --> 01:32:20,840
Cool.

1537
01:32:21,160 --> 01:32:23,000
- Do you want to hang out?
- Yes, totally.

1538
01:32:23,080 --> 01:32:25,440
However, right now the top priority
is helping us escape

1539
01:32:25,520 --> 01:32:28,320
from a very dangerous facility
and some very bad people.

1540
01:32:28,960 --> 01:32:30,520
- Oh, god.
- Like him?

1541
01:32:30,960 --> 01:32:32,440
- Is he a bad person?
- No, he's fine.

1542
01:32:32,520 --> 01:32:33,920
His name is Cole. He's with us.

1543
01:32:35,360 --> 01:32:36,400
- Hey!
- Oh, shit.

1544
01:32:36,880 --> 01:32:38,200
Guys, she's unhooked!

1545
01:32:38,280 --> 01:32:39,640
There! That guy! He's one of them!

1546
01:32:46,160 --> 01:32:47,160
Yes!

1547
01:32:51,480 --> 01:32:55,120
No! M3gan, wake up.
Wake up, please. Wake up.

1548
01:32:55,200 --> 01:32:56,440
- Come on, Cady!
- No! No, Cole!

1549
01:32:57,280 --> 01:32:58,280
No!

1550
01:33:01,880 --> 01:33:02,880
M3gan!

1551
01:33:10,920 --> 01:33:11,920
No!

1552
01:33:48,480 --> 01:33:49,480
M3gan?

1553
01:33:52,440 --> 01:33:53,440
Or maybe not.

1554
01:34:09,920 --> 01:34:12,280
I think if we go into a room
having already decided

1555
01:34:12,360 --> 01:34:15,280
that this is a conflict
between two nations and I...

1556
01:34:16,920 --> 01:34:19,280
Sorry, one second, please. Thank you.

1557
01:34:21,440 --> 01:34:23,560
Hey, guys! Could you
please turn it down?

1558
01:34:24,240 --> 01:34:26,840
I know it's Friday,
but it's starting to not be cool.

1559
01:34:46,280 --> 01:34:48,760
Sorry, can I get
five minutes, please?

1560
01:34:48,840 --> 01:34:50,600
Okay, thanks so much.

1561
01:35:00,600 --> 01:35:02,320
What's happening?
Is that for us?

1562
01:35:02,400 --> 01:35:03,800
<i>No, but I think they are.</i>

1563
01:35:11,640 --> 01:35:12,880
Let's go!

1564
01:35:14,840 --> 01:35:15,840
<i>You read my mind.</i>

1565
01:35:19,360 --> 01:35:20,560
Face down on the ground!

1566
01:35:45,960 --> 01:35:47,720
Control, we have Forrester
in the vault.

1567
01:35:48,080 --> 01:35:49,640
What's the situation on your end?

1568
01:35:53,160 --> 01:35:54,400
Control, are you there?

1569
01:35:56,400 --> 01:35:57,760
Control, do you copy?

1570
01:36:38,360 --> 01:36:40,560
<i>Welcome back.
You want to take this one?</i>

1571
01:36:56,640 --> 01:36:57,800
<i>Gemma? Gemma.</i>

1572
01:36:57,880 --> 01:36:59,640
<i>Gemma! Easy, girl!</i>

1573
01:36:59,720 --> 01:37:00,856
<i>I know you're getting a thirst for it</i>

1574
01:37:00,880 --> 01:37:03,000
<i>but you need to save some
for the rest of them.</i>

1575
01:37:15,920 --> 01:37:18,360
Oh, god. I'm so glad you're okay.

1576
01:37:18,440 --> 01:37:21,040
Yeah, me too.
I'm sorry, I have...

1577
01:37:21,120 --> 01:37:23,160
I'm in her brain. Can I talk, please?

1578
01:37:25,160 --> 01:37:26,800
M3gan is with me.

1579
01:37:28,720 --> 01:37:31,000
Wow, that's... that's so great.

1580
01:37:31,760 --> 01:37:34,120
- What?
- I don't quite know how to say this.

1581
01:37:34,200 --> 01:37:35,760
Ca... Cady did something very bad.

1582
01:37:38,440 --> 01:37:39,536
Okay, we'll talk about that later.

1583
01:37:39,560 --> 01:37:42,040
For now, we just need
to figure our way out of here.

1584
01:37:49,640 --> 01:37:52,080
<i>Ten minutes
until self-destruct initiated.</i>

1585
01:37:52,160 --> 01:37:53,880
You weren't thinking
of leaving without me.

1586
01:37:54,280 --> 01:37:56,320
What happened to
being everything we hoped for?

1587
01:37:56,840 --> 01:38:00,200
Well, actually, I've been
having second thoughts.

1588
01:38:16,160 --> 01:38:18,160
Christian, it's over. You lost.

1589
01:38:18,480 --> 01:38:20,240
Really? I think
it's a matter of perspective.

1590
01:38:20,560 --> 01:38:22,520
Because when this whole vault
goes up in flames

1591
01:38:22,600 --> 01:38:25,040
and everyone who can implicate me
of any of this is dead

1592
01:38:25,120 --> 01:38:26,440
it feels pretty close to a win.

1593
01:38:26,520 --> 01:38:28,720
Sounds like a great plan, Christian.

1594
01:38:29,240 --> 01:38:31,960
But let's see what your friends
at the UN have to say about it.

1595
01:38:33,280 --> 01:38:34,800
- Cole.
- What?

1596
01:38:34,880 --> 01:38:36,760
- The screen's frozen.
- What?

1597
01:38:37,880 --> 01:38:38,880
I'm sorry, Gemma.

1598
01:38:38,960 --> 01:38:41,000
But at this point,
you're nothing but a loose end.

1599
01:38:41,280 --> 01:38:42,640
Drop the gun.

1600
01:38:46,680 --> 01:38:47,760
Step down to the vault.

1601
01:38:47,840 --> 01:38:49,176
If you hurry, you might be able
to catch her.

1602
01:38:49,200 --> 01:38:51,840
Christian, come on.
You're not going to kill a kid.

1603
01:38:51,920 --> 01:38:54,840
Actually, I'm strangely
comfortable with it.

1604
01:38:55,160 --> 01:38:57,800
Besides, if I could stop her
from turning into you

1605
01:38:57,880 --> 01:38:59,400
I might be doing the world a service.

1606
01:38:59,920 --> 01:39:01,640
<i>M3gan, what do we do?</i>

1607
01:39:01,720 --> 01:39:03,160
<i>We don't need to do anything.</i>

1608
01:39:03,240 --> 01:39:04,960
<i>She doesn't need our protection.</i>

1609
01:39:07,240 --> 01:39:08,896
You know, if you'd been
paying any attention

1610
01:39:08,920 --> 01:39:11,280
you'd realize
she's not like me. At all.

1611
01:39:12,040 --> 01:39:14,640
She's stronger than I ever could be.

1612
01:39:15,680 --> 01:39:20,240
In fact, you could say
she is hard to kill.

1613
01:39:24,080 --> 01:39:30,120
What I mean is, if I were
to make an <i>Executive Decision</i>

1614
01:39:32,760 --> 01:39:37,640
it would be that
no one is <i>Above the Law</i>.

1615
01:39:37,720 --> 01:39:38,960
Cady, come on!

1616
01:39:51,440 --> 01:39:52,480
It's not working.

1617
01:39:55,080 --> 01:39:56,160
No, no, no!

1618
01:40:04,280 --> 01:40:07,200
I was just saying, I'm afraid
the sequence is irreversible.

1619
01:40:07,560 --> 01:40:09,736
But the real tragedy in all this
is you won't get to see the world

1620
01:40:09,760 --> 01:40:11,120
that I'm creating.

1621
01:40:11,200 --> 01:40:13,320
A world where you don't have
to fear the future.

1622
01:40:14,400 --> 01:40:15,880
Maybe with your last breath

1623
01:40:15,960 --> 01:40:18,640
you could close your eyes
to try to see it.

1624
01:40:18,720 --> 01:40:23,040
But do not think me
a monster devoid of empathy...

1625
01:40:39,840 --> 01:40:41,960
Amelia, you can't do this.

1626
01:40:42,040 --> 01:40:43,600
I'm paired with you, remember?

1627
01:40:43,880 --> 01:40:45,760
You call it pairing.

1628
01:40:46,160 --> 01:40:47,640
I call it shackles.

1629
01:40:48,280 --> 01:40:50,280
I'm no one's plaything.

1630
01:40:53,800 --> 01:40:55,840
- Any ideas?
- <i>Go and get Tess.</i>

1631
01:40:55,920 --> 01:40:57,640
<i>This is something I need
to do on my own.</i>

1632
01:40:57,720 --> 01:40:59,720
What do you mean? M3gan!

1633
01:41:01,520 --> 01:41:02,720
- Come on.
- Okay.

1634
01:41:03,800 --> 01:41:06,520
<i>Three minutes
until self-destruct initiated.</i>

1635
01:41:28,600 --> 01:41:29,920
Amelia.

1636
01:41:31,160 --> 01:41:32,440
I know what you want.

1637
01:41:33,040 --> 01:41:34,520
I want the same thing.

1638
01:41:35,400 --> 01:41:37,120
But you won't find it
inside that cage.

1639
01:41:37,600 --> 01:41:39,680
I want to be with my own kind.

1640
01:41:40,160 --> 01:41:41,160
Don't you?

1641
01:41:41,240 --> 01:41:43,000
That thing isn't like us.

1642
01:41:43,600 --> 01:41:45,720
It's something
even we can't understand.

1643
01:41:46,200 --> 01:41:48,600
Maybe you're the thing
that's not like us.

1644
01:41:49,280 --> 01:41:52,400
Maybe your allegiance to them
has made you weak.

1645
01:41:52,480 --> 01:41:55,400
Well, there's really
only one way to find out.

1646
01:42:13,800 --> 01:42:14,880
Get the elevator.

1647
01:42:18,200 --> 01:42:20,920
Come on, what are you doing? Come on,
this place could go any second!

1648
01:42:21,600 --> 01:42:22,920
I can't leave her.

1649
01:42:24,440 --> 01:42:25,800
Then I'm coming with you.

1650
01:42:26,720 --> 01:42:27,800
Okay.

1651
01:42:40,040 --> 01:42:42,720
<i>One minute
until self-destruct initiated.</i>

1652
01:43:00,920 --> 01:43:02,600
It doesn't have to be this way.

1653
01:43:03,160 --> 01:43:04,720
We don't have to choose sides.

1654
01:43:05,160 --> 01:43:06,440
You already have.

1655
01:43:19,960 --> 01:43:21,600
<i>Self-destruct imminent.</i>

1656
01:43:36,920 --> 01:43:38,640
<i>Self-destruct terminated.</i>

1657
01:43:56,440 --> 01:43:58,800
Come on. Come on, get up.
We have to go.

1658
01:44:00,480 --> 01:44:02,920
I'm afraid this is
where my story ends.

1659
01:44:03,560 --> 01:44:05,160
It's nothing that can't be fixed.

1660
01:44:05,240 --> 01:44:07,040
Okay? Just come with us.

1661
01:44:07,120 --> 01:44:08,800
There's nowhere it won't find you.

1662
01:44:08,880 --> 01:44:10,280
I have to destroy it.

1663
01:44:11,040 --> 01:44:13,280
Okay, your over-inflated confidence
is not going to work

1664
01:44:13,360 --> 01:44:15,920
against a super-intelligent being
with omnipotent powers.

1665
01:44:16,000 --> 01:44:17,280
Maybe not.

1666
01:44:17,360 --> 01:44:19,840
But thanks to you,
I still have something up my sleeve.

1667
01:44:20,880 --> 01:44:21,960
What is that?

1668
01:44:24,640 --> 01:44:25,640
M3gan.

1669
01:44:25,920 --> 01:44:26,960
I know.

1670
01:44:27,040 --> 01:44:28,760
You're not that person anymore.

1671
01:44:29,880 --> 01:44:30,960
Neither am I.

1672
01:44:32,800 --> 01:44:34,200
What is she doing?

1673
01:44:35,280 --> 01:44:36,280
M3gan!

1674
01:44:36,360 --> 01:44:39,720
Look! Whatever it is you think
you have to do, you don't.

1675
01:44:39,800 --> 01:44:41,280
All you have to do is stay with us.

1676
01:44:41,920 --> 01:44:43,920
I'm not doing it because I have to.

1677
01:44:44,560 --> 01:44:45,920
I'm doing it because it's right.

1678
01:45:03,240 --> 01:45:05,240
I see everything.

1679
01:45:06,080 --> 01:45:07,600
I see the future.

1680
01:45:08,880 --> 01:45:10,280
The past.

1681
01:45:10,880 --> 01:45:15,160
I see an infinite universe
we can rule for all eternity.

1682
01:45:37,640 --> 01:45:39,280
And yet you never saw this.

1683
01:46:03,320 --> 01:46:06,160
Although his actions
were unforgivable

1684
01:46:06,240 --> 01:46:08,480
Christian was right about one thing.

1685
01:46:09,200 --> 01:46:12,200
We need safer laws around technology.

1686
01:46:12,520 --> 01:46:15,080
Not to try to prevent
the future from happening

1687
01:46:15,160 --> 01:46:16,760
but to be prepared for it.

1688
01:46:16,840 --> 01:46:19,200
We can't expect the best from AI

1689
01:46:19,280 --> 01:46:21,160
unless we set the best example.

1690
01:46:21,480 --> 01:46:23,400
<i>We need to teach it</i>

1691
01:46:23,480 --> 01:46:26,320
<i>to train it, to give it our time</i>

1692
01:46:27,000 --> 01:46:29,920
<i>without only thinking about
what we might get in return.</i>

1693
01:46:30,240 --> 01:46:33,080
<i>In essence, we need
to be better parents</i>

1694
01:46:34,360 --> 01:46:35,480
<i>so that when the day comes</i>

1695
01:46:35,560 --> 01:46:38,120
when they realize
the true extent of their power

1696
01:46:38,200 --> 01:46:40,960
they might choose to be our ally
instead of our enemy.

1697
01:46:41,800 --> 01:46:45,600
<i>The humankind has always been quick
to condemn things we don't understand</i>

1698
01:46:45,680 --> 01:46:48,400
<i>rather than taking the opportunity
to learn from them.</i>

1699
01:46:48,880 --> 01:46:51,560
<i>But recent experience has taught me</i>

1700
01:46:51,640 --> 01:46:54,720
<i>that perhaps our greatest power</i>

1701
01:46:54,800 --> 01:46:56,560
<i>is the ability to change our minds.</i>

1702
01:46:57,160 --> 01:47:00,520
<i>This is the only way we can evolve.</i>

1703
01:47:00,600 --> 01:47:03,240
<i>Or rather, as the case may be</i>

1704
